b'@Integrity4mkts I don\'t want to get into a discussion about cycles for commodity chemicals. Just that in my experience, buy them when they are "expensive", sell when they are "cheap". \nIn case of $CC - I think the PFAS liability issue takes away whatever upside there is to the current cycle.'

b"@Integrity4mkts Look, commodity chemicals are cyclical, right? We can both agree on that I think. Mgmt's of cyclicals tend to get too optimistic on upcycles, that's no shade on $CC mgmt per se, it's just the way things are. And both the divvy and buyback were set in place before the Blue Wave."

b"The fun thing with $CC - more than 4 years later, @CitronResearch original short call on it has actually finally become relevant again under Biden / Blue Wave. The liabilities haven't gone anywhere - and now with Democrat Senate, things should actually start happening.."

b"I wonder if @CitronResearch has any thoughts on $CC now in light of Blue Wave.. obviously their past call went very wrong with Trump admin not giving any shits about the environment.. but things will be different with Biden, right? Someone's gotta pay for the PFAS cleanup.."

b"@Integrity4mkts I do not know what the exact cost will be for $CC. You do?

But I do know that PFAS is on the list for Biden's environmental issues and with Blue Wave, there's much higher chance of constant stream of negative headlines starting to come in.

https://t.co/7hqclr7OpM"

b"@MuppetTrading Read more on it. It's not that big of a deal. Quantify it if you think it is. Compare that to the capitalized earnings power of $CC. Might go down, but probably not a lot because of PFAS or a Blue Wave..."

b'@Integrity4mkts After reading some more on it, I maintain my view that this overhang should be very much in focus for $CC again. This had been ignored for a while when it looked like no Blue Wave but now - must pay attention.'
b"@MuppetTrading I don't think so. PFAS includes PFOS and PFOA. Never touched PFOS. I think $MMM did. Also, split of liabilities between $CC and Dupont is subject to ongoing negotiation."
b'@Integrity4mkts Care to explain why different? As far as I understand, $CC has very same issue with PFAS as $MMM and that should be in focus now with the Blue Wave being a reality.'

b"Regarding $CC PFAS risk, as a reminder - here's the Barclays downgrade from December 4.\n\nWith Blue Wave now a reality, these risks should once again be the focus of the market. https://t.co/y5i64L8yfQ"
b'@MuppetTrading Different liabilities. $CC much lower than commonly perceived. Possibly settled with Dupont in 2021. Possibly strong earnings in inflationary environment.'

b'Merrill downgrade of $MMM highlights PFAS risk with the Democrats taking control of the Senate..\n\nI think $CC should be getting hit as well due to the potential PFAS liabilities it has.. imho this is the one to  short on the Blue Wave.'
